This paper is about improving the performance of neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The proposed model involves splitting the decode state into two parts and updating them in different time-scales, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also leverages information in different granularities, which is a common theme in neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
